hat provides payment links, invoices, quotes, subscription management, and automation and revenue reporting; and breeze, an AI that powers the customer platform that provides AI-powered insights, automation, content generation, and data enrichment, as well as Breeze Assistant, a go-to-market assistant to boost productivity and make work easier; and Breeze Agents, which helps teams automate work end-to-end from strategy to execution. In addition, the company provides professional services to educate and train customers on how to utilize its CRM platform; and customer success; phone and/or email and chat-based support services; and helps customers by providing Customer Success Manager and Partner Development Manager digital channels through educational content academey. It serves mid-market business-to-business companies. The company was incorporated in 2005 and is headquartered in Cambridge, Massachusetts.","industry":"Software - Application","sector":"Technology","marketCap":10393249792,"trailingPE":106.857895,"forwardPE":13.003233,"pegRatio":0.32,"priceToBook":5.2825627,"priceToSales":3.151261,"profitMargin":3.04,"operatingMargin":3.2960000000000003,"grossMargin":83.655,"returnOnEquity":5.011,"returnOnAssets":1.0980001,"revenueGrowthYoy":23.400000000000002,"earningsGrowthYoy":null,"earningsQuarterlyGrowthYoy":null,"debtToEquity":12.384,"currentRatio":1.609,"quickRatio":1.348,"freeCashFlow":656183360,"operatingCashFlow":797971968,"totalCash":1691052032,"totalDebt":247291008,"revenue":3298124032,"dividendYield":null,"payoutRatio":0,"beta":1.229,"fiftyTwoWeekHigh":626.935,"fiftyTwoWeekLow":173.25,"targetMeanPrice":280.16333,"targetHighPrice":450,"targetLowPrice":180,"recommendationKey":"buy","numberOfAnalystOpinions":33,"lastQuarter":{"date":"2026-03-31","period":"-1q","epsActual":2.72,"epsEstimate":2.46745,"surprisePct":10.24},"earningsHistory":[{"date":"2025-06-30","period":"-4q","epsActual":2.19,"epsEstimate":2.12399,"surprisePct":3.11},{"date":"2025-09-30","period